Introduction

Lai Kuan Lin is a Taiwanese rapper, singer, and actor. He is best known for being a member of the project group Wanna One after competing on Produce 101 season 2. He debuted with Wanna One on August 7, 2017, with the mini album 1X1=1 (To Be One).

After the group disbanded, he formed a duo with PENTAGON's Wooseok. Known as Wooseok X Kuanlin, they debuted on March 11, 2019, with the mini album 9801.

In July 2020, Kuanlin requested to terminate his contract with his former agency, Cube Entertainment, citing violations of contract and the sale of his management rights to a third party. On June 17, 2021, the Seoul Central District Court ruled in his favor, allowing him to terminate his contract with Cube.
